# Why: HTML <title>, <meta name="description">, OG (og:title, og:image,
#      og:description), and Twitter (twitter:site, twitter:card) tags all
#      hard-code "Documenso" branding from upstream. This overlay swaps them
#      for Pacta brand strings sourced from packages/lib/constants/app.ts
#      (overlay 021).
#
#      Specific changes:
#        - Page title format: "{page} - Documenso" → "{page} - Pacta"
#        - Default title: "Documenso" → "Pacta"
#        - Description: long upstream marketing blurb → short Pacta tagline
#        - og:title: "Documenso - The Open Source DocuSign Alternative"
#                  → "Pacta — Agreements that hold"
#        - twitter:site: "@documenso" → "@bizrethink"
#        - author: "Documenso, Inc." → "BizRethink AI"
#        - keywords: rewritten to focus on multi-tenant + audit-trail story
#
#      What stays unchanged: the og:image / twitter:image references the
#      same `/opengraph-image.jpg` filename. The actual JPEG file gets
#      replaced separately as part of the asset commit (Pacta lockup over
#      charcoal background).
#
#      Fragility: LOW-MED. Upstream rarely touches meta.ts, but if they add
#      new tags we need to merge in the new entries. Conflicts are easy to
#      resolve — keep ours, ignore theirs.
#
diff --git a/apps/remix/app/utils/meta.ts b/apps/remix/app/utils/meta.ts
--- a/apps/remix/app/utils/meta.ts
+++ b/apps/remix/app/utils/meta.ts
